<paragraph blockId="33.[397,805,220,243]" box="[397,805,220,243]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308">
<heading box="[397,805,220,243]" centered="true" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" reason="5">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Chapuis, 1875" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[460,805,220,243]" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini Chapuis, 1875</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="308" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[113,1089,267,1058]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,224,267,290]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308">Remarks.</emphasis>
This tribe is assemblage of three groups previously considered as distinct tribes: Asterizini, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[237,424,299,322]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1942" box="[484,617,299,322]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Physonotini">Physonotini</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="BOROWIEC" box="[630,819,299,322]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" pagination="541 - 558" refId="ref48083" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1995: Tribal classification of the cassidoid Hispinae. Pp. 541 - 558. In: PAKALUK J &amp; SLIPINSKI S. A. (eds): Biology, Phylogeny and Classification of Coleoptera. Papers Celebrating the 80 th Birthday of Roy A. Crowson. Volume 1. Muzeum i Instytut Zoologii PAN, Warszawa, xii + 558 pp." type="book chapter" year="1995">BOROWIEC (1995)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that all three should be united because of lack of synapomorphies based on adult characters and used the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[178,362,363,386]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
as the valid name. 
<bibRefCitation author="BOROWIEC" box="[570,765,363,386]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC (1999a)</bibRefCitation>
also considered the three taxa synonymous, however, used 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1942" box="[423,550,395,418]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Physonotini">Physonotini</taxonomicName>
as the valid name because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[846,1030,395,418]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
were based on a genus that was a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gistel, 1834" authorityName="Gistel" authorityYear="1834" box="[597,846,427,450]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Eurypedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[597,710,427,450]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="308">Eurypedus</emphasis>
Gistel, 1834
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Spaeth, 1942" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1942" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Physonotini">
Physonotini 
<bibRefCitation author="Spaeth" box="[113,251,459,482]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" pagination="11 - 43" refId="ref51435" refString="SPAETH F. 1942: Cassidinae (Col. Chrysom.). Pp. 11 - 43. In: TITSCHACK E. (ed.): Beitrage zur Fauna Perus. Nach der Ausbeute der Hamburger Sudperu-Expedition 1936, anderer Sammlungen, wie auch auf Grund von Literaturangaben. Band II. Lief. 1. Conradt Behne, Hamburg." type="book chapter" year="1942">Spaeth, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed after 1930 without description or bibliographic reference to such description thus being unavailable (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[500,630,491,514]" firstAuthor="ICZN" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" refId="ref49784" refString="ICZN 1999: International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
: Article 13.1) and therefore the name was recently changed again to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[393,577,523,546]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BOUCHARD" box="[592,825,523,546]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="BOUCHARD" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" pagination="1 - 972" refId="ref48757" refString="BOUCHARD P., BOUSQUET Y., DAVIES A. E., ALONSO-ZARAZAGA M. A., LAWRENCE J. F., LYAL C. H. C., NEWTON A. F., REID C. A. M., SCHMITT M., SLIPINSKI S. A. &amp; SMITH A. B. T. 2011: Family-group names in Coleoptera (Insecta). ZooKeys 88: 1 - 972." type="journal article" year="2011">BOUCHARD et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[113,1089,267,1058]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[144,328,555,578]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
are superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[615,714,555,578]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
and are quite difficult to define and separate from the latter tribe based solely on adult morphology. 
<bibRefCitation author="SWIETOJANSKA &amp; WINDSOR" firstAuthor="SWIETOJANSKA" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" pagination="641 - 665" refId="ref51716" refString="SWIETOJANSKA J. &amp; WINDSOR D. 2008: Immature stages of Asteriza flavicornis (Olivier) and Physonota alutacea Boheman (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Annales Zoologici (Warszawa) 58: 641 - 665." type="journal article" year="2008">ŚWIĘTOJAŃSKA &amp; WINDSOR (2008)</bibRefCitation>
discussed their position based on larval morphology and concluded that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
possessed features characteristic for primitive (generalized) tribes of Cassidinae s. str. while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[177,276,683,706]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
were considered as derived. The head of adult specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[905,1088,683,706]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
is more similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1942" box="[305,458,715,738]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Goniocheniini">Goniocheniini</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hincks" authorityYear="1952" box="[491,605,715,738]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Omocerini">Omocerini</taxonomicName>
as the head is distinctly transverse with small eyes situated in front of the mouthparts, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[633,732,747,770]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
have circular head, mostly with large eyes. In addition all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[392,576,779,802]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
have simple and quite long tarsal claws and the ultimate tarsomere is somewhat longer than in most 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[661,760,811,834]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
and as a result they are capable of faster movement than most of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[468,571,843,866]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
. Also the larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[777,961,843,866]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
move more rapidly than those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[340,439,875,898]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
(L. Sekerka, unpubl. observation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[113,1089,267,1058]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308">
Two genera, 
<taxonomicName authority="Spaeth, 1911" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[275,493,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,354,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="308">Orexita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Spaeth" box="[359,493,907,930]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">Spaeth, 1911</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Spaeth, 1952" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1952" box="[539,751,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aidoia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[539,609,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="308">Aidoia</emphasis>
Spaeth, 1952
</taxonomicName>
, currently classified in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[985,1085,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
, have a strongly transverse head with small eyes and similar structure of tarsi as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
and I transfer them to the latter tribe. The affinity of the two genera to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[908,1089,971,994]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
as well as affinities of the genera within the tribe should be verified by molecular data. The genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[220,404,1035,1058]" pageId="33" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
can be recognized using the key below.
</paragraph>
